#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
PENELOPE Simulation Studio V9  (PySide6)
======================================
Two-tab GUI for PENELOPE2011 simulations.

Tab 1  Geometry Viewer
   Open / edit a .geo file in a syntax-highlighted editor
   "Render 2D" / "Render 3D" use the internal Studio renderer.
   "Native 2D" / "Native 3D" open an in-studio bridge to PENELOPE's
    native gview2d.exe / gview3d.exe for Fortran-side checks.
   Image updates only when you click Render  never automatically.

Tab 2  Simulation (.in) Editor
   Full text editor for the .in file
   Smart-edit toolbar with one-click commands:
      Change Particle     SKPAR  prompt
      Change Energy       SENERG prompt
      Set Source Pos      SPOSIT prompt
      Set Beam Cone       SCONE  prompt
      Add Material        MFNAME + MSIMPA prompts
      Set Geometry File   GEOMFN prompt
      Set Sim Showers     NSIMSH prompt
      Set Time Limit      TIME   prompt
   Each command finds the existing line and replaces it,
    or appends before END if not found.
   Run Simulation button launches penmain / penelope executable.

Requirements
------------
  pip install PySide6

Usage
-----
python penelope_studio_v9_split_runs_patch_v2.py
python penelope_studio_v9_split_runs_patch_v2.py myphantom.geo mysim.in
"""

